      <title>[Letter] 1835 Jan. 30, Carthage [to] Adam Fergusson, Legrange, Tennessee / Louisa C Jones</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is two letters, the first is written by Adam Fergusson, and the second is written on the reverse side, and is dated January 30, 1835 from Louisa C. Jones to Adam Fergusson. In the first letter Fergusson discusses his experiences and good prospects in Mississippi. Jones' letter is an expression of affection and longing to see her sister again.</abstract>
